                            <comment id="468986" author="simmonsja" created="Tue, 26 Aug 2025 16:22:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As you can see I pushed a patch but currently its broken due to other router related works being in flight. We will have to wait until Chris Horn new work lands before pushing an update.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="468950" author="gerrit" created="Tue, 26 Aug 2025 14:10:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;James Simmons &amp;lt;jsimmons@infradead.org&amp;gt;&quot; uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/60909&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/60909&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18544&quot; title=&quot;route import with NID-range is not working&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18544&quot;&gt;LU-18544&lt;/a&gt; utils: handle special lnetctl import for route setup&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 232bc60092600813b855e8326477958dc380458d&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="465281" author="simmonsja" created="Tue, 29 Jul 2025 13:05:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That is strange. I just tested current master and I see&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;lnetctl import ~/route.conf &#160;&#160;&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
&#8212; &lt;br/&gt;
add:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;import: &#160;&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;errno: -22 &lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;descr: ! &quot;gateway is invalid key&quot; &lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I also test lnetctl route add with a NID range so that works correctly. Looks like its a matter of intercepting the import command for routes and alter the YAML config being sent.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="465274" author="simmonsja" created="Tue, 29 Jul 2025 12:50:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There are a few issues here. First is that&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;gateway: 10.151.0.&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;@o2ib&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;is considered invalid YAML syntax. The characters [ and , are considered special and if you want them to be considered as literal then it should be:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;gateway: &quot;10.151.0.&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;@o2ib&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;libyaml should report an error without the double quotes.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Second I need to look at passing in a netmask. We have partial support of this but its more testing if an new NID address is in the range support.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In our case we need to pass in the NID with netmask up to the kernel and then internally calculate the first and last address. Then add all the addresses in that range. I can break up the work into different pieces for each step.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="464211" author="simmonsja" created="Fri, 18 Jul 2025 17:51:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry I can look at this. Just give me a few days.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="464206" author="sthiell" created="Fri, 18 Jul 2025 17:10:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issues reported here (silent fail and lack of range support) are present in Lustre 2.16 and this is an annoying regression vs. 2.15. Any progress?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="438439" author="simmonsja" created="Fri, 13 Dec 2024 00:18:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Once the netmask work lands we can fix this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
